                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13892375" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 18:07:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At least one problem is that in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6385&quot; title=&quot;FD phi estimator initial conditions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6385&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6385&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we never converted the initial value to nanos, so when we divide by the mean when the only sample is the initial value and thus equivalent to it, the resulting phi is inflated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13892450" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 19:18:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nit: shouldn&apos;t we use TimeUnit to convert instead of hardcoding extra constants?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13892522" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 20:25:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 removes the constant &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4925&quot; title=&quot;Failure Detector should log or ignore sudden time change to the past&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4925&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4925&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added and uses TimeUnit instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893802" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 20:59:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893804" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 21:00:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this affects 1.2 as well&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893807" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 21:03:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1.2 doesn&apos;t use nanos, so I don&apos;t think so.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893809" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 21:05:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, you&apos;re right.  It was a bad merge.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893813" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 21:08:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
